# Star Citizen Data Sources

When needing Star Citizen game data (components, shops, mining, ships, etc.), check these repos **first** before web searching:

## Primary Data Repos

### 1. richardthombs/scunpacked
**URL:** https://github.com/richardthombs/scunpacked

Main game data extracted from Star Citizen files. Key files in `api/dist/json/`:
- `shops.json` - Shop inventories and locations (~12MB)
- `items.json` - All game items (~15MB)
- `ship-items.json` - Ship equipment index
- `ships.json` - Ship data
- `manufacturers.json` - Manufacturer info
- `starmap.json` - Location data

### 2. seneca0815-rgb/SC_Signature_Scanner
**URL:** https://github.com/seneca0815-rgb/SC_Signature_Scanner

Mining RS signature data:
- `lookup.json` - 163 signature values for 26 minerals × 6 multipliers

## Usage Pattern

1. Identify what data is needed
2. Check if scunpacked has it (most game data)
3. Check SC_Signature_Scanner for mining signatures
4. Only web search if neither repo has the data

## Notes

- scunpacked data is extracted from game files, so it's authoritative
- Hand-mineable gems share base RS 620 (not useful for identification)
- Ship-mineable ores each have unique signatures (3170-4300 range)
